.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Build output + deps — Vercel builds remotely, never upload these. A local
# `.next` (~500MB after a local build) bloats the tar and times out the upload.
.next
node_modules

# Local dev/agent artifacts — never deploy (transient sqlite files break the tar)
.code-review-graph
graphify-out
.claude
.smart-hook
.serena
.playwright-mcp
.git.corrupt.bak
.agents

# Untracked local scratch — keep out of production builds.
# NOTE: anchor screenshot PNGs to the repo ROOT (leading slash). A bare
# `*.png` matches recursively and would strip public/connector-logos/*.png,
# 404-ing every connector logo in production.
/*.png
wbuy-after.md
src/app/preview

# macOS "Keep Both" duplicates (e.g. "page 2.tsx") — never real route/source.
# They get type-checked by `next build` and a stale copy fails the whole build.
* 2.ts
* 2.tsx
